You are on a walkway.
You can see a poster.
You can go west, north or south.
You push open the door and step out into the hallway -- and nearly stumble into the void!

"Crumbs!" you swear, catching yourself before you step off the walkway and tumble to your death. Looking around, you see that the asylum is built into the walls of a towering, hollow basalt structure.  Doors set into the inner walls, which presumably lead to rooms, are connected by a rickety metal walkway circling the inside of the structure... but, without any sort of railing or fence, one wrong step and you could well fall right off the edge! Rising up from the pit in the center of the asylum, you see a tower holding up a small structure lined with black, reflective windows -- that must be the panopticon where Dr. Caligazzi lives. You notice that the central panopticon is connected to the walkway by four bridges, each at one of the four cardinal directions.

"I say, keep away from the edges, Rags!" says Percy, "It's a long way down!"

"Yeah, you don't gotta tell me again."
> x poster

> x poster
Someone has pasted a broadsheet poster to the stone wall here, possibly some sort of PSA for the asylum staff. It's got some little drawings of various urchins on it -- including a mug that you recognize as your own! --  so it's probably a listing of the best, most duckiest urchins!
> ask Percy about poster

> ask Percy about poster
"Aw, criminy, this poster is fulla letters! How in Sam Hill am I spos'd ta read THAT?" "Calm down, Rags, I'll help you out," says Percy, "This is just your standard wanted poster courtesy of the Urchinfinder General. It says:" OFFICIAL PROCLAMATION!! The Office of the Urchinfinder General issues the following warning to be on the watch for certain street urchins of sordid reputation and mischievous intent. The top ten most wanted urchins are wanted for crimes of truancy, lollygagging, apple-snatchery, boodling, doodling, humbugging, jitterjamming, and general mopery. DO NOT APPROACH! If seen, contact your nearest Urchinfinder or Pinkerton agent.  So signed,Ursula Earlgrey, Urchinfinder General

"Top 10 Most Wanted Street Urchins, by order of the Urchinfinder General.
10. Long Tall Oswald
9. Beefy Josiah Oxtail
8. Hector the Vector
7. Herman the Vermin
6. Transgender Mordecai
5. The Dapper Lads, individually known as Silent Calvin and Miss Trix
4. Two-Eyed Mulligan
3. The Straggletag
2. Lil' Ragamuffin
1. Nasty Mac"

"Sorry, Rags," says Percy, "Looks like you're still only second best."

"Criminy! Wot's a gal gotta do ta be number one? One a' these days I'll pull a prank so mischievous, I'll knock dat Nasty Mac right offa his perch!"
> ask Percy about Nasty Mac

> ask Percy about Nasty Mac
"Why is Nasty Mac Public Enemy Number 1?  Wot's he done that I ain't done?"

"Well, Rags, Nasty Mac is wanted for hooliganism, rough-housing, boodling, bootlegging, rowdiness, shenanigans, yanking on Sandy Perkins' pigtails, stealing apple pies left to cool on windowsills, capering, clowning, buffoonery, knocking President Hoover's trilby off with a slushball, arson, and, worst of all, causing a general ruckus.  It would be hard to be a bigger nuisance than Nasty Mac."

"Fine, fine, forget I asked," you mutter.
> ask Percy about urchinfinder

> ask Percy about urchinfinder
"Ah yes, Rags, the Urchinfinder General. Director of all the national urchin culling efforts and only fourth in line for the presidency -- after the Vice President, the Overpope, and the Grand Inquisitor. If she's designated you Public Enemy Number 2, you really should try to keep a lower profile."

"I should be Public Enemy Number 1," you say, "Wot's them other urchins done that I ain't done?"

"Sorry, Rags, I guess you're just not that much of a menace to the peace yet!"
