You are in a therapy room.
You can see Precious Violet, a teapot and Darling Jeremiah.
You can go east.
The therapy room is a large, brightly lit room; unlike the cells, the walls here are painted a calming institutional green. Crayon drawings -- presumably by patients -- plaster the walls.  The floor underneath is a plush shag carpet that feels warm and soft to your bare feet after the chilly metal of the outside walkway.

To one side, two kids of about your age sit at a low wooden table, fidgeting with tea cups.
> x Violet

> x Violet
Precious Violet is a short, squat, freckle-faced girl in a freshly-pressed white blouse and navy blue pinafore, her brown hair pulled back in twin pigtails.  Her face is fixed in a wide grin. She clutches her teacup in one shaking hand, compulsively bringing it to her mouth and sipping "pretend" tea over and over.
> x Jeremiah

> x Jeremiah
Darling Jeremiah is a small towheaded boy wearing a crisply-ironed sailor suit, his white cap set at a jaunty angle on his head. His face is frozen in a rictis grin and, even when he's facing straight towards you, his unnervingly blue eyes never quite seem to focus on anything.
> x teapot

> x teapot
It's a simple ceramic teapot with a pretty flower painted on the side. It's full of imaginary tea, as you call it, nothing.
> speak to Violet

> speak to Violet
"Tea is life, tea is the blood of my mother and father, pumping through the veins of the universe, I shalln't want for naught but tea," she mutters under her breath. You have no idea what she's talking about.
> speak to Jeremiah

> speak to Jeremiah
"Oh my, a visitor!" Darling Jeremiah carefully places his teacup on the table and turns to face you. "We're ever so pleased to be charmed to make your acquaintance! I am Darling Jeremiah and this delightful young lady with me is Precious Violet. How do you do, indeed?"

"Er... I does good, thanks. I is Lil' Ragamuffin, the toughest urchin west o' the Potomac, an' this is me pal, Percy."

"Sir Percival Throckmorton Scruffs III, if you please," interjects Percy.

You roll your eyes. There he goes, gettin' all fancy. "Yeah, yeah, wot he said."

"Oh dearie me, an urchin? How dreadful!" says Darling Jeremiah. "We won't have any of your mischief here! We're good little children!"
> ask him about Violet

> ask him about Violet
"Precious Violet used to be a most dreadful urchin, given to all sorts of unspeakable mischief. But, as you can see, the good doctor's therapy has helped us both realize that we would much rather be good little children rather than nasty urchins!"
> ask him about Himself

> ask him about Himself
"Twas a time that I was known as Jimmy Throatpunch, the two-fisted terror of the East Side! But those days are far behind me now. Thanks to the good doctor, I've realized that it's much better to be well-behaved than naughty."
> ask him about doctor

> ask him about doctor
