> x table

> x table
The table is covered in straps and restraining belts, leading you to believe it probably wasn't used for much examination but rather a more "shocking" purpose. Noded wires, no doubt intended to be fixed on a patient's forehead, lie across the table, attached to the electroconvulsive therapy machine against the wall.
> x machine

> x machine
A large machine, dominating nearly the total wall of the room, covered in dials and gauges. The orderly on duty could crank up the electricity by turning a large ship's wheel mounted on the machine's control panel.

