> put chicken on table

> put chicken on table
You drop the cold roast chicken on the examination table and attach the electrical nodes to its body. This outta get this bird jumpstarted! Now you just need a current...
> turn wheel

> turn wheel
You grab the wheel and throw all your weight into cranking it. The wheel moves slowly with a loud grinding noise, the wires on the examination table starting to leap and spark, the crackle of electricity in the room starting to intensify.  Suddenly, a great crackle of electricity jumps from the machine, traveling down the wires and shocking the cold roast chicken.

The lights flicker and sparks fly. You're forced to jump back, releasing the wheel, but the damage is done.  The roast chicken's giblets have been shocked into working order, and the carcass jumps off the examination table, bursting free from the nodes and wires, and starts running around in circles.
> take carcass

> take carcass
