"Vot? Vot do you talk about, leetle girl?" grunts the matron, but she turns to look. As soon as her back is turned, you unplug the dropper bottle and dump all its contents into her postum mug.

"I do not see any president dance," says the matron, turning back to eye you suspiciously. She raises her coffee mug to her lips and takes a sip. "Vot is your game, leetle girl?"

Moments later, an uncharacteristically concerned look passes over the nurse's craggy features. Her stomach gurgles urgently. "I must...go now," she mutters, knocking over her chair as she rises to her feet and runs off.
