You can go east.
The control room is a darkened room filled with switches, levers, and fuse boxes, none of which make any sense to you. The air crackles with electricity, so much so that you can feel your bare toes tingling and your hair standing on end.
> x switch

> x switch
It's a heavy iron switch, so big that it looks like it would take two hands to pull.

"That's the incinerator switch," says Percy helpfully. "The label says: Warning! High voltage! Handling switch without proper gloves may result in immediate electrocution!"
> wear stocking

> wear stocking
"Crumbs, Percy, I'll bet this'll work jest fine fer a glove!" you say, pulling the worn stocking over your arm and up to your shoulder.
> pull switch

> pull switch
You grab the switch and immediately feel the crackle of live electricity, numbing your digits and making your hair stand on end. Luckily, the stocking provides just enough insulation that you don't immediately die.

You give the switch a mighty tug, but nothing happens. You try again, this time lifting your feet from the floor and letting your full weight dangle from the switch. That does the trick! Slowly, grindingly, the enormous switch starts to move down until it finally reaches the off position.

You let go and drop back to the floor just as your stocking glove bursts into flames.  With a yelp, you throw it to the floor and stomp the fire out. Youch!
