You are in the Panopticon.
You can see Dr. Belladonna Caligazzi and telescopes.
You can go west, east, north or south.
The panopticon is a small, cramped room, just big enough to accommodate a desk, a chair, and an astounding variety of surveillance equipment.  Various telescopes of varying types and strengths are set up round the room's perimeter, pointing out in all directions, so that Dr. Caligazzi can watch the comings and goings of the asylum through the dark tinted glass windows.

Currently, Dr. Caligazzi is hunched over her desk, working her way through a stack of papers with a rubber stamp.

She looks up from her paperwork.  "Ah, if it isn't the second most wanted urchin in all of Garbagetown! I can see why you're so high on the list."

"Should be first," you mutter under your breath,

"I admit, I didn't expect you to actually make it this far. I've been keeping an eye on you and it's proven most interesting. You really are a resourceful little thing, aren't you? Nevertheless, I'm afraid it won't do you any good.  Feel free to keep exploring, because I'm afraid that you won't actually be leaving the asylum since you would need discharge papers signed by me. And I certainly won't be signing anything to allow a dangerous and mischievous urchin like you to get out of here!"
> x doctor

> x doctor
Dr. Belladonna Caligazzi is the director of St. Hesper's Asylum for the Criminally Mischievous. She is a mature woman clad in a tightly buttoned white lab coat, wearing high black boots and her hands hidden in black rubber gloves. Her dark black hair just starting to streak gray.
> x telescopes

> x telescopes
In theory, you could see anything in the asylum if you looked through the right telescope at the right time.
