You are in an elevator.
You can see an elevator operator.
You can go south.
It's little more than a small box of corrugated iron and metal mesh, just big enough for two people. An eager elevator operator waits for your instructions, his hand gripping the operations lever in readiness.

"Hey Mac, where ya wanna go? The observatory? The penthouse? The vestibule? Heeeey, wait a sec, whadya tryin' ta pull here, Mac? You don't look like no doctor! You look like a patient! Did they let ya out?"

"Yeah, that's right! They said 'Ain't no use tryin' ta keep Lil' Ragamuffin, the number one most wanted urchin, locked up, so we mighta well just let ya go! So jest take me down ta the lobby an' I'll be on my way."

"Huh. I thought Lil' Ragamuffin was the number TWO most wanted urchin...."

Maybe he sees the murder in your eyes because he quickly changes the subject. "But anyways, I can't take ya nowhere without seein' some discharge papers signed by the boss."

> x operator

> x operator
The elevator operator is a spiffy young man with slicked-down black hair and a wide eager smile, dressed in a dashing red bellboy hat and vest.
> speak to operator

> speak to operator
He doffs his cap. "Speedy's the name, elevator operatin's the game!"
> give papers to operator

> give papers to operator

"I got 'em right here, smart guy!" you crow, waving the discharge papers in Speedy's face.

He scans them quickly. "Alright that looks all in order. Where to, kid?"

"Take me down ta th' lobby! I'm outta here!"

"You got it, kid." He throws the switch and the elevator lurches to life, groaning and creaking as the metal mesh doors slide shut and the shuttle begins to descend.

Finally, the elevator hits the ground with a jolt.  Speedy pries the doors open.

You step out. Freedom!

You step outside, inhaling deeply of the briny salt air. Turning around, you see the towering edifice of St. Hesper's asylum -- from the outside, it looks like a towering black basalt column, indistinguishable from a natural tower except for the odd chink in the cliff face here and there that denotes a window. Ahead of you, you see the beach. In fact, all around you is ocean. Looks like the asylum is built on a tiny island off the Maryland coast. No worries there. You're pretty confident you can swim that stretch back to the mainland. After all, you ARE an urchin.

Behind you, Speedy throws the elevator lever in reverse. The elevator's mesh doors close, but before he can ascend you shout out to him.

"Oy! Speedy!"

"What's that? What can I do ya for, kid?"

You point at his face and laugh. "Ha ha! Guess what, ya mook? I tricked ya! I wasn't discharged at all. I jest escaped!"

Speedy's eyes bulge. "What?! No way, Dr. Caligazzi would never..."

"The doctor's gonna be mighty sore when she wakes up an' sees I've gone and skadoodled! But whaddya gonna do about it? I is out like a whale oil lamp!"

Giggling, you scamper off down the dunes, making straight for the crashing waves.

"Did you really need to rub his face in it?" asks Percy, "The last thing we need is him sounding the alarm before we're even off the island."

"Eh, wot's he gonna do? Ain't no body can catch Lil' Ragamuffin the urchin.... twice, at least!  Pretty slick for the number TWO most wanted urchin, eh? Maybe now you'll think about bumpin' me up ta number ONE!"

"Well, we can only hope so," sighs Percy.

"Hold on tight, Percy, we's goin' in the drink!"  You laugh as you jump into the surf, but no time for talking now. You've got to swim.

You paddle off against the waves, a free urchin again.
